History of Present Illness: 
I saw NADINE AGUILAR in the office today for an ini tial consultation.  She is a 66 year old  woman wit h 
the complaint of low back pain involving the latera l aspects of her lower extremities to the dorsum of  the 
feet.  The legs bother her equally and bother her j ust as much is the lower back.  She has intermitten t 
numbness, tingling, and weakness of the legs and us es a front wheeled walker.  She has no best positio n 
and therefore can have pain with sitting, standing,  walking, and lying down.  She denies any bowel 
incontinence but has had urinary incontinence for 5  years. 
She has not undergone physical therapy but did go t o a chiropractor without relief.  She has not had 
injections done.  She takes ibuprofen.  
She takes Norco 10/325 4 per day and Motrin 800 mg daily. 
She has not had a recent MRI of the lumbar spine.  Her lumbar spine x-rays done at AVMC on February 5 
reveal narrowing of the L5-S1 interspace with a lis thesis at L4-5.
